OL,3,CTearful interview of woman accused of
OL,4,Cmurdering husband played to court
OL,6,FWhen asked if she had stabbed her
OL,7,Fhusband, Mrs Rawle said: "I must have,
OL,8,FI was the only one there."
OL,10,FThe jury had been read a catalogue of
OL,11,Ftext messages chronicling three years
OL,12,Fbetween Mr and Mrs Rawle.
OL,14,FThroughout, there were endearments
OL,15,Fbetween the two of them, but as the
OL,16,Ftime went on, there were a number from
OL,17,FMrs Rawle accusing her husband of
OL,18,Fbeing weak, feeble, a pathetic excuse
OL,19,Fof a man.
